cs.LG, cs.CR, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.SI

This paper is about a Python library for secure and explainable machine learning. It covers topics such as attacks against machine learning models, security evaluation, and explainability. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses security and attacks, which suggests the sub-category cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) as the second most likely. Additionally, the paper mentions deep neural networks and visualizations, which are related to the sub-categories cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision), respectively. Finally, the paper includes explainability methods, which could be relevant to the sub-category cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
